@startuml
autonumber
actor "Prosumer" as Actor

box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box

box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "Prosumer MS" as PMS
end box

box "Data Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS" as DBp
end box

note over Actor, DBp: Decommissioning/Deregistration process follows the same information flow but using operators like DELETE

== Prosumer Registration ==
Actor -> Camunda: Prosumer Register
Camunda -> Kong: POST /Prosumer
Kong -> PMS: Forward Request
PMS -> DBp: JDBC INSERT INTO Prosumer: \n(Name, Fiscal ID, Location, Payment Details)
DBp --> PMS: 200 OK
PMS --> Kong: 201 Created
Kong --> Camunda: 201 Created
Camunda --> Actor: Successful Registration

== Asset Registration ==
Actor -> Camunda: Register Asset
Camunda -> Kong: POST /Prosumer/{prosumerId}/assets
Kong -> PMS: Forward Request
PMS -> DBp: JDBC INSERT INTO Asset: \n(AssetID, ProsumerID, AssetType, Model, Status)
DBp --> PMS: 200 OK
PMS --> Kong: 201 Created
Kong --> Camunda: 201 Created
Camunda --> Actor: Asset Successfully Added
@enduml